"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-09-Chinese-paper-cutting-artistry-shines-at-Paris-Olympics-1vV8gsHa0P6-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  As the Paris Olympics is abuzz with excitement, Shen Yanli, a talented paper-cutting artist from Huzhou in east China, infuses her unique flair into this global celebration of sportsmanship and athleticism. Her exquisite paper-cuttings showcase traditional designs like the \\\"Mulberry Fish Dragon\\\" and the 2024 Olympic mascot, Phryge, seamlessly blending Chinese and French elements. These worksare being showcased at iconic landmarks including the Arc de Triomphe and the Eiffel Tower by students from her hometown.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"